<br>
thanks   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jefm>jefm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/1/02 3:52:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2055.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Traditional</span><hr size=1> Well...traditionally no computers are involved...<br>
the pictures are drawn then the cels are coloured then they take thousands of photographs...so what you're seeing is basically a slide show of thousands of paintings...<br>
with computers in general most of it is the same process except the cels are scanned digitally...recently a few all computer examples like &quot;blood: the last vampire&quot; have appeared...but still it's usually done pretty traditionally with computer graphics as eyecandy...<br>
so basically...if you want to be an animator you'll get used to sore hands...<br>
if you want to do stuff like they have at newgrounds...use flash...<br>
and what they use to show the images so fast???...<br>
Ummm usually it's all hardware...a film projector...or a vhs or dvd player....it's all done in hardware..really it sounds impressive but go buy a pad of post-its and draw on the bottom bit...frame by frame...just stick people or something lame...that's classic animation and that is still how most film projectors work.. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=chikin>Chikin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/1/02 6:22:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2055.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://homepage.ntlworld.com/spoonofdoom/dogtopus.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Traditional</span><hr size=1> A lot of anime now is done digitally, I think. Angelic Layer had the keyframes sketched, and then inked &amp; shaded on computer. I would have thought it'd just be output digitally after that. Dunno what software/hardware though, something pretty specific methinks. If you wanna do some anime youself, macromedia director or flash are probably your best options. It won't look totally professional, but done right it can look pretty damned cool and be exhibited on the web to boot. ^^ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jefm>jefm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/2/02 8:41:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2055.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   studios</span><hr size=1> different studios do it different ways...<br>
studio ghibli I belive still does it mostly traditionally...they do use a lot of computers but I believe it's done a lot by hand...<br>
Disney last i checked was almost totally traditional...of course some scenes are done digitally but a lot of it is just scanned digitally and put with thest so they can arrange them and toy with hem on a computer...<br>
a really neat example is fox animation's anastasia...the computer work was really subtle...they used a lot...but for the most part it was traditional...<br>
computers still tend to be used as a garnish...mostly because of the temptation to have perfect looking images mixed with normal animation looks bad...if they made the computer stuff more beat up and crappy looking...or if they went to straight cell style...everything would work well...Blood was done very well....titan AE...was not...both were decent movies but the transition from 2d to 3d was too harsh in the latter <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zhandvega>Zhan Dvega</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://zettai.homestead.com/files/Rose.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/2/02 5:34:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2055.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://zettai.homestead.com/files/sidesmall.gif height=89 width=67></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: studios</span><hr size=1> Bleh, for the most part I like my cartoons computer free (why I always revel in watching old-school Anime) except for a few... exceptions... Like Cowboy Bebop... Ohh that was done well... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jefm>jefm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/2/02 7:48:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2055.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Well</span><hr size=1> there's probably a few surprises...like mononoke...that used computers very heavily...<br>
most modern animation is done digitally....it makes the whole process easier and faster... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wyers>Wyers</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/3/02 12:01:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2055.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Well</span><hr size=1> if the technology is there...use it...<br>
but i dont like 3d scenes in a cartoon...kind of defeats the point...<br>
3d animation = cool<br>
2d animation = great<br>
mix = annoying...<br>
<br>
examples  =  vandread and initial d<br>
<br>
its ok when they blend them together well....in zoids it looks cool...but when its obvious, i get a little x vein on my forhead <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=chikin>Chikin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/4/02 2:27:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2055.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://homepage.ntlworld.com/spoonofdoom/dogtopus.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Well</span><hr size=1> Yeah, I agree, 3D animation looks kinda weird. In Full Metal Panic sometimes it looks alright, othertimes just plain TERRIBLE. It's like &quot;painted backgrounds, cel people....3D STUDIOOOO......painted backgrounds...&quot;<br>
<br>
The stuff I've been most impressed with 3D wise is Invader Zim and Futurama. I'm surprised that isn't used more often actually, 'cos that slots in more or less perfectly. I'm sure that with a little more tweaking it'd ROCK. :D <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=psoj>psoj</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/7/02 1:10:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2055.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://menotu.homestead.com/files/goku.jpeg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Well</span><hr size=1> ummmm...you make key poses you scan em the computer does the rest pretty much now adays...as for how many drawings are in each...WB did it on 2s so you hold an image for 2 frames which makes it about 15 images per second (30fps regular tv time if i remember right) * 60 seconds = 90 fpm * a regular 15 to 30 minute show....950 to 1080 images per show...<br>
<br>
usually the artists only do the keys and the inbetweens...other than that the computer does the rest, but with certian motions more is needed, take any of disney's movie for example, each character moves in very different ways the computer doesn't pick up on anything accept that it is not in there so if you want that little goofy hand to go up and bend back you gotta drw it like at before coming back....<br>
<br>
as for what programs animaters use...well any number of programs it's all a matter of budget and what your going for, but most 3D animaters use 3DStudio Max or Maya...for 2D Lightwave and a couple others but i don't remember them too good...the program i used whas just a camera hooked into a computer that shot one frame when you clicked the button and then allowed you to put it on a tape..., but there are also other ways..like you can scan 60 images and put them in a javascript loop on a webpage and after all the images load it would look just like it was a animated gif... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=retrotorque>RetroTorque</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/7/02 4:48:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2055.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.liquid2k.com/solidnate/vsig.gif height=106 width=106></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: how do they make anime cartoons?</span><hr size=1> I bet they use a image compiler like Adobe Premier to make editing easier. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=chikin>Chikin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/7/02 7:15:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2055.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://homepage.ntlworld.com/spoonofdoom/dogtopus.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: how do they make anime cartoons?</span><hr size=1> Heh, they wouldn't use Premier. There's better stuff than that, custom built machines &amp; things. :) <br>
<br>
*hates premier in all it's crashingeveryfivesecondsevilness*<br>
<br>
but yeah, it'd probably be something similar. I'd be surprised if anything was analogue now. :\ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=defcombeta@polykarbonbbs>defcombeta</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/8/02 1:55:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2055.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_smile.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: how do they make anime cartoons?</span><hr size=1> try using a avid editor suit ( thry thz sound as standard and the viewer is 1/2 the size of a cinema screen. if yur semi pro try razor or mac final cut pro is good for getting experinece <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showPrevMessage?topicID=2055.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showNextMessage?topicID=2055.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2055.topic&index=11><img src=http://www.polykarbon.com/bbsimage/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.emailToFriend?topicID=2055.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.threadControl?topicID=2055.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a